olin is a way of mocking those who are sad and emotional.\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most sports fans\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3350}, {\"ngram\": \"the violin\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3381}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Djokovic has done the violin celebration all summer for his daughter, who has taken up the instrument.\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3439, \"end\": 3447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.230260265575606e-17, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the violin celebration\", \"from\": 3457, \"to\": 3479}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter\", \"from\": 3495, \"to\": 3507}, {\"ngram\": \"the instrument\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A more socially savvy superstar would have recognized that even though he won, the moment belonged to Nadal, and all he had to do was not step on it.\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0137280528729004e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A more socially savvy superstar\", \"from\": 3543, \"to\": 3574}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 3622, \"to\": 3632}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then again, a more socially savvy superstar would have come up with a different celebration in the first place, just so nobody would mistake the message.\", \"from\": 3693, \"to\": 3846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a more socially savvy superstar\", \"from\": 3705, \"to\": 3736}, {\"ngram\": \"a different celebration\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3784}, {\"ngram\": \"the first place\", \"from\": 3788, \"to\": 3803}, {\"ngram\": \"nobody\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3819}, {\"ngram\": \"the message\", \"from\": 3834, \"to\": 3845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surely there are ways for Djokovic to connect with his daughter without irritating anybody else.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3873, \"end\": 3881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.230260265575606e-17, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3868}, {\"ngram\": \"his daughter\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"anybody\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 3937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic is no villain.\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Djokovic\", \"from\": 3945, \"to\": 3953}, {\"ngram\": \"no villain\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a relentless competitor and a gracious loser, and he can be charming and even sweet.\", \"from\": 3969, \"to\": 4059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a relentless competitor\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3998}, {\"ngram\": \"a gracious loser\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a temper, but tennis has seen far worse; Djokovic\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s moments of on-court petulance would have earned Jimmy Connors and John McEnroe points for good behavior.\\u00c2 Djokovic just has a remarkable tendency to make himself look bad at the most inopportune times.\", \"from\": 4060, \"to\": 4323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4169, \"end\": 4182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Connors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmy Connors\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Connors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Connors\"}, {\"begin\": 4187, \"end\": 4199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John McEnroe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McEnroe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a temper\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4075}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4087}, {\"ngram\": \"Djokovic\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s moments\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"court\", \"from\": 4135, \"to\": 4140}, {\"ngram\": \"good behavior\", \"from\": 4211, \"to\": 4224}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2 Djokovic\", \"from\": 4225, \"to\": 4235}, {\"ngram\": \"a remarkable tendency\", \"from\": 4245, \"to\": 4266}, {\"ngram\": \"the most inopportune times\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He engages with hecklers, or in the case of Casper Ruud\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fans at Wimbledon, people Djokovicimaginesto be hecklers.\", \"from\": 4324, \"to\": 4441, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hecklers\", \"from\": 4340, \"to\": 4348}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 4356, \"to\": 4364}, {\"ngram\": \"Casper\", \"from\": 4368, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"Wimbledon\", \"from\": 4392, \"to\": 4401}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4403, \"to\": 4409}, {\"ngram\": \"Djokovicimaginesto\", \"from\": 4410, \"to\": 4428}, {\"ngram\": \"hecklers\", \"from\": 4432, \"to\": 4440}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He mocks the celebrations of opponents who are nowhere near his equal, as he did with Ben Shelton at last year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s U.S. Open.\", \"from\": 4442, \"to\": 4567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4528, \"end\": 4539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\", \"score\": 0.9999837952540147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Shelton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Shelton\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the celebrations\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4467}, {\"ngram\": \"opponents\", \"from\": 4471, \"to\": 4480}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S. Open\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic became the best player in the world after most fans had already fallen for Nadal or Federer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094or both.\", \"from\": 4569, \"to\": 4680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4653, \"end\": 4658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0137280528729004e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Djokovic\", \"from\": 4569, \"to\": 4577}, {\"ngram\": \"the best player\", \"from\": 4585, \"to\": 4600}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4613}, {\"ngram\": \"most fans\", \"from\": 4620, \"to\": 4629}, {\"ngram\": \"Federer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094or\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So admiration came later than it should have, and his anti-vaccination stance alienated a lot of fans.\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4783, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"admiration\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4694}, {\"ngram\": \"his anti-vaccination stance\", \"from\": 4731, \"to\": 4758}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 4769, \"to\": 4774}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4782}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If he resents being the best player ever but the third-favorite of his generation, that is his right.\", \"from\": 4784, \"to\": 4885, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best player\", \"from\": 4804, \"to\": 4819}, {\"ngram\": \"his generation\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4865}, {\"ngram\": \"his right\", \"from\": 4875, \"to\": 4884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Djokovic could have done himself a favor Monday by looking across at Nadal and realizing that will be him before long.\", \"from\": 4887, \"to\": 5009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4891, \"end\": 4899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.230260265575606e-17, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 4960, \"end\": 4965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0137280528729004e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a favor\", \"from\": 4924, \"to\": 4931}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is 37.\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5019, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Nadal said after the match, speaking only of his own inevitable retirement: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThat's part of life.\", \"from\": 5020, \"to\": 5122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5023, \"end\": 5028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0137280528729004e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 5040, \"to\": 5049}, {\"ngram\": \"his own inevitable retirement\